WEEKLY ANNOUNCEMENTS

Washington County Early College High School
**Thursday, August 27, 2020 at 7:00 pm - Drive-In National Honor Society Induction for the 11 students from last spring. Students, please dress for the occasion, (pictures will be taken), wear a mask, and stay in your car until directed to get out. Someone will assist you with parking when you arrive. Please be on campus by 6:50 pm.
**Any student interested in joining the WCECHS Student Government Association this year should check out the announcement on the Early College's webpage.

**Seniors - A list of scholarships is available and more scholarships will be added throughout the school year. Please visit the W.C. Early College High School webpage then click Administration. There you will see a link entitled Seniors. Look at the very top for a scholarship link. Please check that out!
**Each of you should be working on completing your NC Residency forms for Financial Aid. Please give us a call if you need assistance at 252-793-1327. I hope everyone has a great week.

post_text:
BCCC College Textbooks
Hello WCECHS Parents, Scholars and Staff,
We apologize for the delay in textbooks but here is the current status.
1). Students may begin picking up college textbooks at 8:30 am on Tuesday August 18, 2010. The bookstore at BCCC has had an unexpected shut down. The vice president for academic has communicated with every BCCC instructor about the delay.
2). If you have a textbook from a previous semester then you must turn that book in or pay the replacement cost. You will not be allowed to pick up your books until this is clear. All students on that list will receive a phone call tonight at 7:30.
3). We may not have all textbooks in by Tuesday but I assure you that this is a top priority. If you run into any problems because of textbooks then please reach out to me or Mr. Lewis via email.
Thank you. Have a great weekend.
Mr. W. Price. #WOLVES

Pre-Kindergarten Applications
GREETINGS! The Washington County School Pre-Kindergarten program still has openings available for the 2020-2021 school year. Pre-K parents your child will have the option of either face-to-face instruction or virtual instruction, beginning on August 17, 2020. The application can be dropped off at the Central Support Services office located at 802 Washington Street Plymouth, NC 27962.
For more information please contact Mrs. DaShonda Riddick at our Central Office at 252-793-5171 or via email at dkeyes@wcsnc.org. Please follow us on Facebook, Twitter and our Washington County Schools Website.

🚨 Graduation Announcement 🚨

WCHS will host a drive in graduation for our seniors on May 22, 2020 at 6:00 pm. We will not have any public participation. Graduation will be live streamed and broadcast on Magic 95.9 FM for family and friends afar. The live stream can be located on the district webpage at www.wcsnc.org. Seniors are asked to arrive to the school by 5:15pm. Immediately following graduation the students will participate in a parade through town; the route will go down Third Street then to the downtown Plymouth area. This route has several open parking lots. We are asking everyone to stay in their vehicles and follow all safety guidelines.

If we have rain, we will have a drive-thru graduation.

Important Dates and Times
Graduation Practice - May 21, 2020 at 3:00 pm
Graduation- May 22, 2020 6:00 pm
Seniors please return chromebooks and athletic uniforms by May 20, 2020.

CLASS OF 2020 - “WCHS C/O 2020 Adopt a Senior”

“WCHS C/O 2020 Adopt a Senior”
The administrative staff of Washington County High School was inspired to start “WCHS C/O 2020 Adopt a Senior”. As you know, our seniors scholars will not have the traditional memorable graduation activities and ceremonies, due to the COVID-19 pandemic.
We are asking OUR COMMUNITY to help by ADOPTING A SENIOR during these times. Senior Scholar information is posted on “WCHS C/O 2020 Adopt a Senior” Facebook page. The gift(s) you choose to give does not have to be expensive. Any ACT OF KINDNESS your heart leads you will be greatly appreciated. Some suggestions could be a gift card, cash app or gift basket.
Thanking you all in advance for lifting the spirits of our Class of 2020 senior scholars.
DISCLAIMER: Any and all information about our senior scholars are at the discretion of their parent or guardian.

Good Morning WCS Families!
This is another reminder that we will be starting meal delivery at 10:00 am this morning. Please check the county website for routes to determine what time will be at your home or call the school for assistance. As a reminder, a student does need to be at the road for the bus or at their normal bus stop to get meals. Please contact the bus garage if you do not have a stop at your home today. See you curbside today at 10:00 am!
Have a great day!
--------------
¡Buenos días familias de WCS!
Este es otro recordatorio de que esta mañana comenzaremos a entregar las comidas a las 10:00 am. Consulte las rutas del sitio web del condado para determinar a qué hora será en su hogar o llame a la escuela para obtener ayuda. Como recordatorio, un estudiante necesita estar en la carretera para tomar el autobús o en su parada normal de autobús para recibir comidas. Póngase en contacto con el garaje del autobús si no tiene una parada en su casa después de hoy. ¡Nos vemos hoy a las 10:00 de la mañana!

¡Que tengas un gran día!

Hello Parents and Guardian of WCS Students,

We are continuing our meal delivery service tomorrow, March 24, 2020. Please check the WCS website for a bus delivery schedule close to your home. Each household's address is not listed, but if students are standing outside, the bus will stop and provide a meal.

Please have someone standing outside so the bus knows to stop. Thanks for your cooperation as we seek to serve all of our families during this time.
----------------------------------

Hola padres y tutores de estudiantes de WCS,

Continuaremos con nuestro servicio de entrega de comidas mañana, 24 de marzo de 2020. Consulte el sitio web de WCS para ver el horario de entrega de autobuses cerca de su hogar. La dirección de cada hogar no figura en la lista, pero si los estudiantes están parados afuera, el autobús se detendrá y ofrecerá una comida.

Haga que alguien se pare afuera para que el autobús sepa que debe detenerse. Gracias por su cooperación mientras buscamos servir a todas nuestras familias durante este tiempo.

Good Evening Parents / Guardians,

Washington County Schools values stakeholder input and believes that collaboration makes us stronger. The Calendar Committee is asking that staff, students, parents, and community members take part in the Washington County Schools 2020-2021 Calendar Survey. Please complete the survey at http://bit.ly/WCS2021calendar. The survey will remain open until Monday, March 9th, 2020 and we look forward to receiving your feedback. Thank you.

Buenas tardes padres / tutores,

Las Escuelas del Condado de Washington valoran los comentarios de las partes interesadas y creen que la colaboración nos hace más fuertes. El Comité del Calendario solicita que el personal, los estudiantes, los padres y los miembros de la comunidad participen en la Encuesta del Calendario 2020-2021 de las Escuelas del Condado de Washington. Complete la encuesta en http://bit.ly/WCS2021calendar. La encuesta permanecerá abierta hasta el lunes 9 de marzo de 2020 y esperamos recibir sus comentarios. Gracias.

Hello Parents, Guardians, and WCS Staff,
WCS will have an early release day on tomorrow, Thursday February 20, 2020 due to the incoming weather. A decision for Friday Mandatory Teacher Workday for staff will be made Thursday evening. Please see the section for early dismissal on WITN Channel 7, WNCT Channel 9 and MAGIC 95.9. Please plan accordingly.
Early release times: Elementary/Middle Schools - 12:15 pm
High School - 12:55 pm
Early College - 11:55 pm

WCS tendrá un día de lanzamiento temprano mañana, jueves 20 de febrero de 2020 debido al clima entrante. Por favor planifique en consecuencia.

Preparatoria - 12:55 pm
Early College - 11:55 pm
